cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper presents an unsupervised learning algorithm for training agents to achieve goals without hand-crafted rewards or expert data. The paper focuses on reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm presented in the paper involves training a goal-conditioned policy and a goal achievement reward function, which are both learned simultaneously. This suggests that the paper could also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also applies the algorithm to three different domains, including Atari, the DeepMind Control Suite, and DeepMind Lab, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper involves optimizing a co-operative game, which suggests that it could also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
